FeedPackage.Description:
TK.CustomMap provides the following enhancements to the Xamarin.Forms.Maps.Map:
- Bindable Pins - Bindable Map Center - Bindable Selected Pin - Hide Pins - Change Icons of pins - Make Pins draggable - Map Long Press Command - Map Clicked Command - Drag End Command
TK.CustomMap also provides the possiblitly to send requests to the Google Places API to get place predictions.
FeedPackage.Summary: Extended Map Control of the Xamarin.Forms.Maps.Map
FeedPackage.Tags: xamarin pcl xam.pcl plugin for plugin map android xamarin.forms ios monoandroid monodroid monotouch
FeedPackage.Title: TK.CustomMap

FeedPackage.Description:
TK.CustomMap provides the following enhancements to the Xamarin.Forms.Maps.Map:
- Bindable Pins - Change Image of Pins - Make Pins Draggable - Hide Pins - Bindable Selected Pin - Bindable Map Center - Bindable Routes - Bindable Circles - Bindable Polygons - Map Commands - Long Press - Click - Pin Selected - Drag End - Pins Ready - Callout click
Extra Features: - Google Maps Places API Wrapper(API Key needed) https://developers.google.com/places/ - Get Place predictions - Get Place details Google Maps Directions API Wrapper(API Key needed) https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/directions/ - Calculate Routes OSM Nominatim API Wrapper http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Nominatim - Get Place predictions
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
[1.1.0] Beta Release
New: - OSM Nominatim API Wrapper - Google Maps Directions API Wrapper - Adding Circles, Routes and Polygons to the map - Callouts can be clicked Fixed: - Clearing an observable Collection of Pins will now update the map correctly
FeedPackage.Summary: Extended Map Control of the Xamarin.Forms.Maps.Map
FeedPackage.Tags: xamarin pcl xam.pcl plugin for plugin map android xamarin.forms xamarin.forms.maps extended custom ios monoandroid monodroid monotouch
FeedPackage.Title: TK.CustomMap

FeedPackage.Description: Titanium is a collection of language bindings for the Botan cryptography library. Currently, ISO C++ and .NET 4.5 are supported. There are plans to add support for Windows Runtime. Please note that not all features of Botan are supported. This is due to the interoperability requirements of Titanium. However, we welcome pull requests that expand on the level of integration supported by Titanium.
FeedPackage.Title: Titanium.NET
